<b>Foods to Eat</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">During this condition, large amounts of histamine are produced by the immune system when the body comes into contact with an allergen. Quercetin is a type of polyphenol that can help control the levels of histamine being produced by the body. Onions, garlic, peppers, and beans are some of the common examples of the same.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">However, Vitamin C is a natural antihistamine to counteract these effects.Congestion is often a big problem for people with allergic rhinitis, but the spice can sometimes help with the problem. The compound can be helpful when we are feeling congested as it breaks down mucus, causing it to run.</span>

